Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveThe PDP in Delta State has announced a new date for the run-off primary election for Okpe/Sapele/Uvwie and Ethiope Federal Constituency.
A statement by Ifeanyi M. Osuoza, state publicity secretary, said the exercise will come up at Sapele Township Stadium and Oghara Township Stadium on May 24.
The rerun will feature, among other contestants, Erhiatake Ibori-Suenu, the daughter of the state’s former Gov. James Ibori who failed to defeat her challenger Ben Rolland in the first run for the Ethiope Federal Constituency ticket on Sunday.

Both tied with 34 votes each.
The first poll produced no clear winner for ticket, as the two contestants, tied at the end of the contest held in Oghara, Delta State, with 34 votes each.
‘All House of Representatives Aspirants, Independent National Electoral Commission, INEC, and Security Agencies should please take note,” Osuoza said.
